1 olive oil
2 potato
1 capsicum
1 packet pork mince
½ tin Crushed & Sieved Tomatoes
20 g butter
1 tsp brown sugar
2 Butter Burger Buns
1 bag Shredded Cabbage Mix
1 drizzle white wine vinegar
1 packet garlic aioli
1 sachet All-American Spice Blend
1 packet Worcestershire sauce
1 packet Shredded Cheddar Cheese

• Preheat oven to 240°C/220°C fan-forced. Cut
potato into fries.
• Place fries on a lined oven tray. Drizzle with
olive oil, season with salt and toss to coat.
• Bake until tender, 20-25 minutes.

• Meanwhile, finely chop capsicum.

• In a large frying pan, heat a drizzle of olive oil
over medium-high heat. Cook capsicum until
tender, 4-5 minutes.
• Add pork mince and cook, breaking up with a
spoon, until just browned, 4-5 minutes.
• SPICY! This is a mild spice blend, but use less if
you're sensitive to heat! Add All-American spice
blend and cook until fragrant, 1 minute.

• Add crushed & sieved tomatoes (see
ingredients), Worcestershire sauce, the butter
and brown sugar and simmer, stirring, until
slightly reduced, 1-2 minutes. Season to taste.
• Remove pan from heat, sprinkle over shredded
Cheddar cheese and cover with a lid (or foil),
allowing cheese to melt.

• Halve burger buns and bake directly on a wire
oven rack until heated through, 2-3 minutes.
• Meanwhile, combine shredded cabbage mix
and a drizzle of white wine vinegar and olive oil
in a large bowl. Season to taste.

• Top bun bases with American pork and capsicum
mixture, along with some shredded cabbage.
• Serve with fries, garlic aioli and any remaining
shredded cabbage. Enjoy!

TIP: Store any leftover filling in the fridge for
another meal!